{{Infobox person |name=Beck Bennett | image = Beck Bennett by Gage Skidmore.jpg | caption = Beck Bennett in 2017 | birthname = Christopher Beck Bennett | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1984|10|1}} | birth_place = [[Wilmette, Illinois]], U.S. | occupation = Actor, writer, comedian | years_active = 2005–present }}
'''Christopher Beck Bennett''' (born October 1, 1984) is an American actor, writer, and comedian who is a current cast member on [[Saturday Night Live|''Saturday Night Live,'']] joining in [[Saturday Night Live (season 39)|2013]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://splitsider.com/2013/08/here-are-your-new-snl-featured-players/|title=Here Are Your New ‘SNL’ Featured Players|date=2013-08-23|work=Splitsider|access-date=2018-01-21|language=en-US}}</ref> Before his tenure on ''SNL,'' he was recognized for the [[AT&T]] "It's Not Complicated" commercials where he interviewed kids,<ref>{{cite web|last=Nudd |first=Tim |url=http://www.adweek.com/news/advertising-branding/how-att-got-kids-make-some-years-best-ads-148605 |title=How AT&T Got Kids to Make Some of the Year's Best Ads |publisher=Adweek |date=2013-04-15 |accessdate=2013-10-16}}</ref> his sketch videos with the comedy group Good Neighbor,<ref>{{cite web|last=Forde |first=Kevin |url=http://www.cracked.com/blog/the-8-best-internet-sketch-troupes-whose-initials-arent-tam/ |title=The 8 Best Internet Sketch Troupes Whose Initials Aren't TAM |publisher=Cracked.com |date= |accessdate=2013-10-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Perkins |first=Colin |url=http://splitsider.com/2010/10/sketch-artists-good-neighbor/ |title=Sketch Artists: Good Neighbor Adds Some Absurdity to Viral Videos |publisher=Splitsider |date=2010-10-05 |accessdate=2013-10-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.g4tv.com/videos/35689/good-neighbor-sketch-comedy/ |title=Good Neighbor Sketch Comedy |publisher=G4tv.com |date=2008-12-19 |accessdate=2013-10-16}}</ref> and his YouTube show ''Theatre of Life.''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NAqZ-GAVaz0|title=More Theatre of Life|last=beckbennett|first=|date=2011-01-30|website=YouTube|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-06-04}}</ref>
==Early life== Bennett was born in [[Wilmette, Illinois]] (a suburb of [[Chicago]]), the son of Sarah and Andy Bennett. He performed in multiple shows at Children's Theatre of Winnetka.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://childrenstheatrewinnetka.com|title=Children's Theatre of Winnetka|website=Children's Theatre of Winnetka}}</ref> He graduated from [[New Trier High School]] in 2003 where he played [[Jean Valjean]] in his school's production of ''[[Les Misérables (musical)|Les Misérables]]''.<ref name="chicagotribune1">{{cite news|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2013-01-30/entertainment/ct-ent-0131-att-ads-beck-bennett-20130130_1_att-ads-little-kids |title=Beck Bennett's calling answered with AT&T ads - Chicago Tribune |publisher=Articles.chicagotribune.com |date=2013-01-30 |accessdate=2013-10-16}}</ref> Beck attended the [[USC School of Dramatic Arts]] in the B.F.A. Acting program.<ref name="chicagotribune1"/>
==Career== In 2003, Bennett joined the improv/sketch group [[Commedus Interruptus]] along with [[Kyle Mooney]] and [[Nick Rutherford]]. In 2007, after graduation, Mooney, Rutherford, and Bennett joined with editor/director Dave McCary to form the sketch group Good Neighbor.<ref name="chicagotribune1"/> The group received praise from comedian [[Louis C.K.]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/IAmA/comments/tmlnp/louis_ck_reddit/c4nwatc |title=codythebeau comments on Louis C.K. reddit |publisher=Reddit.com |date=2012-05-14 |accessdate=2013-10-16}}</ref> and director [[Steven Spielberg]], who sent Mooney, Bennett, Rutherford, and McCary a personal acknowledgement after being impressed with the ''[[Hook (film)|Hook]]'' parody, ''Unbelievable Dinner''. He complimented the sketch and encouraged the group to continue making funny movies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.schubas.com/Mobile/Show+Details?showId=15276 |title=Schubas |publisher=Schubas |date=2012-01-06 |accessdate=2013-10-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Sykes |first=Tom |url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2013/04/09/beck-bennett-meet-that-guy-in-those-adorable-at-t-commercials.html |title=Beck Bennett: Meet That Guy in Those Adorable AT&T Commercials |publisher=The Daily Beast |date=2013-04-09 |accessdate=2013-10-16}}</ref>
In 2011, Bennett created the satirical political talk show ''Fresh Perspectives'',<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/04/07/fresh-perspective-libya-kids-video_n_846345.html |title='Fresh Perspective' On Libya Offered By Adorable Kids (VIDEO)|publisher=Huffingtonpost.com |date= 2011-04-07|accessdate=2013-10-16 |first=Katla |last=McGlynn}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Hampton |first=Adele |url=http://thehill.com/video/campaign/219231-a-7-year-olds-take-on-mitt-romneys-candidacy |title=A seven-year-old's take on Mitt Romney's candidacy - The Hill's Video |publisher=Thehill.com |date=2012-03-30 |accessdate=2013-10-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/07/01/fresh-perspective-kids-talk-medicare_n_888735.html |title='Fresh Perspectives' Kids Talk Medicare, Call Paul Ryan A 'Lame Doo Doo' (VIDEO) |publisher=Huffingtonpost.com |date=2011-07-01 |accessdate=2013-10-16 |first=Christine |last=Friar}}</ref> which helped him land his AT&T commercials interviewing children.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/07/03/business/media/a-spokesman-finds-fame-interviewing-tiny-experts.html?pagewanted=all&_r=0|author=Stuart Elliott|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|title=A Spokesman Finds Fame Interviewing Tiny Experts|accessdate=2013-10-16|date=2013-07-02}}</ref>
In 2012, he appeared in the film ''Kill Me Now'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hex19.com/blog/kill-me-now-internet-sketch-comics-make-a-movie.html |title=Kill Me Now: Internet Sketch Comics Make A Movie - Geekblog - Hex19 &#124; Celebrating All Things Geek |publisher=Hex19 |date=2012-07-26 |accessdate=2013-10-16}}</ref> a film starring multiple internet sketch-comedy groups, and filmed ''[[Beside Still Waters (film)|Beside Still Waters]]''<ref>{{cite news|author=Jeff Sneider |url=https://variety.com/2012/film/news/chris-lowell-sets-feature-directorial-debut-1118054877/ |title=Chris Lowell sets feature directorial debut|newspaper=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=2012-05-31 |accessdate=2013-10-16}}</ref> by writer/director [[Chris Lowell]].
In March 2013, Bennett appeared in an episode of ''[[Last Man Standing (U.S. TV series)|Last Man Standing]]'', and that August voiced a character for [[Animation Domination|FOX ADHD]]'s ''[[Axe Cop (TV series)|Axe Cop]]''. That same year Good Neighbor produced a pilot for [[Comedy Central]] with [[Adam McKay]]'s [[Gary Sanchez Productions|Gary Sanchez]] production company, though it was not picked up as a series, in light of the move of three of the troupe's four members to New York City to star on ''Saturday Night Live''.<ref name="splitsider1">{{cite web|url=http://splitsider.com/2013/08/good-neighbor-is-the-new-lonely-island-snl-hires-director-dave-mccary-alongside-two-cast-members/|title=Good Neighbor Is the New Lonely Island: 'SNL' Hires Director Dave McCary Alongside Two Cast Members|last=Frucci|first=Adam|date=2013-08-23|publisher=Splitsider|accessdate=2013-10-16}}</ref> That same year Bennett completed work on the [[independent film]] ''[[Balls Out (2014 film)|Balls Out]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2G20709KbfM |title=Intramural: The Movie - 5 Questions w/ Beck Bennett |publisher=YouTube |date=2013-08-01 |accessdate=2013-10-16}}</ref> and appeared in season 4 of ''[[Arrested Development (season 4)|Arrested Development]].''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uproxx.com/tv/2013/05/heres-every-single-arrested-development-season-4-guest-star/|title='Arrested Development' Season 4 Guest Star List|last=Kurp|first=Josh|date=2013-05-08|publisher=Uproxx.com|accessdate=2013-10-16}}</ref>
Bennett voices [[Launchpad McQuack]] in the 2017 ''[[DuckTales (2017 TV series)|DuckTales]]'' reboot.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://screenrant.com/ducktales-reboot-2017-preview-images/|title=DuckTales Reboot Teaser Confirms Summer 2017 Premiere Date|date=7 December 2016|publisher=}}</ref>
'''''<big>Saturday Night Live</big>'''''
Bennett debuted as a featured player on ''Saturday Night Live'' on September 28, 2013.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/09/29/tina-fey-snl-new-cast-members_n_4010798.html|title=Tina Fey Introduces New 'SNL' Cast Members In Season 39 Premiere|date=2013-09-29|work=Huffington Post|access-date=2018-01-21|language=en-US}}</ref> He was promoted to repertory status for ''Saturday Night Live's'' [[Saturday Night Live (season 41)|41st season]] in 2015.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://splitsider.com/2015/10/snl-promotes-beck-bennett-and-sasheer-zamata-to-repertory-players/|title=‘SNL’ Promotes Beck Bennett and Sasheer Zamata to Repertory Players|date=2015-10-05|work=Splitsider|access-date=2018-01-21|language=en-US}}</ref>
His celebrity impressions on ''SNL'' include [[Ashley Parker Angel]], [[Javier Bardem]], [[Bill Belichick]], [[Wolf Blitzer]], [[Jeb Bush]], [[Drew Carey]], [[Bill Clinton]], [[Harry Connick Jr.]], [[Bing Crosby]], [[Guillermo Del Toro]], [[Jim Gilmore]], [[Roger Goodell]], [[Mark Halperin]], [[Philip Seymour Hoffman]], [[Paul Hollywood]], [[Matt Iseman]], [[Ronny Jackson]], [[Elton John]], [[Brian Kilmeade]], [[Steve Kroft]], [[Howie Long]], [[Al Michaels]], [[Jim Nantz]], [[Kevin O'Leary]], [[Nick Offerman]], [[Mike Pence]], [[Vladimir Putin]], [[Jake Tapper]], [[Malcolm Turnbull]], and [[George Zimmer]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://snlarchives.net/Cast/?BeBe|title=SNL Archives {{!}} Cast {{!}} Beck Bennett|website=snlarchives.net|access-date=2018-01-28}}</ref>
'''Recurring characters'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://snlarchives.net/Cast/?BeBe|title=SNL Archives {{!}} Cast {{!}} Beck Bennett|website=snlarchives.net|access-date=2018-01-21}}</ref> * Casey, co-host of ''Inside SoCal'' * Richard Patterson (a.k.a. "Baby Boss"), a successful business executive who has the body and awkward movements of a baby * Jack Trask, host of ''Action 9 News at Five'' * [[Vladimir Putin]], President of the Russian Federation
==Personal life== On May 13, 2016, Bennett posted to his Instagram a photograph of himself with his girlfriend [[Jessy Hodges]], in which the caption stated that the couple were celebrating five years with each other.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BFU7ZM3gVOg/?hl=en&taken-by=beckbennett|title=Instagram post by @beckbennett • May 13, 2016 at 12:17am UTC|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2018-01-28}}</ref> He has been friends with fellow ''SNL'' cast member [[Kyle Mooney]] since they were students at the [[University of Southern California]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dailytrojan.com/2011/01/23/student-comedy-group-grabs-attention/|title=Student comedy group grabs attention {{!}} Daily Trojan|date=2011-01-23|work=Daily Trojan|access-date=2018-01-21|language=en-US}}</ref>
